Introduction

Video games are a rich area for data extraction due to its digital nature. Notable examples such as the complex EVE Online economy, World of Warcraft corrupted blood incident and even Grand Theft Auto self-driving cars tells us that fiction is closer to reality than we really think. Data scientists can gain insight on the logic and decision-making that the players face when put in hypothetical and virtual scenarios.

In this Kaggle Dataset, I provide over 720,000 competitive matches from the popular game PlayerUnknown’s Battlegrounds. The data was extracted from pubg.op.gg, a game tracker website. I intend for this data-set to be purely exploratory, however users are free to create their own predictive models they see fit.

https://www.kaggle.com/skihikingkevin/pubg-match-deaths/home

Choose data

pubg_using_data <- as.data.frame(cbind(pubg_match_deaths$game_size, pubg_match_deaths$party_size, pubg_match_deaths$player_dist_ride, pubg_match_deaths$player_dist_walk, pubg_match_deaths$player_dmg, pubg_match_deaths$player_kills, pubg_match_deaths$player_survive_time))

Data Cleaning

summary(pubg_using_data$`player survive time`)
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
## 0.000e+00 2.470e+02 6.530e+02 8.351e+04 1.299e+03 6.365e+10
pubg_sub <- filter(pubg_using_data, pubg_using_data$`player survive time` < 2500)

pubg_party_size <- as.factor(pubg_sub$`party size`)
str(pubg_party_size)
##  Factor w/ 3 levels "1","2","4": 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 ...
level <- c("SOLO", "Duo", "Squad")
levels(pubg_party_size) <- level
str(pubg_party_size)
##  Factor w/ 3 levels "SOLO","Duo","Squad": 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 2 ...

Explore the data

The Time of Game - box plot

boxplot(pubg_sub$`player survive time`, col = "lightblue", main = "Players' Survival Time" , ylim = c(0, 2500), ylab =  "Time")

Player Kills - histogram

hist(pubg_sub$`player kills`, xlim = c(0,13), col = 0:15, ylab = "the number of player", xlab = "the number of player be killed", main = "Histogram of Player Kills")

Team Tpye - bar plot

barplot(prop.table(table(pubg_party_size)), ylim = c(0, 0.7), main = "Team Tpye", names.arg = c("Solo","Duo","Squad"), col = c("orange","purple","blue"), ylab = "percant of team member")

The Time of Player Survival With Their Damage - scatter plot

plot(pubg_sub$`player damage` ~ pubg_sub$`player survive time`, ylab = "player damage", xlab = "player survive time", main = "The Time of Player Survival With Their Damage")

Conclusion

  1. the most of player play a game in 4min to 38min
  2. the most of player do not kill a number of people in games
  3. players like to play with others
  4. player damage will increace by player survive time before 28min
